d.
Deferred payment sale – is any kind of sales transaction in which the payment of sales
consideration is deferred over a fixed credit term, in installments or on a lump sum basis;

e.
Fair value – The price that would be received to sell an asset or paid to transfer a liability in
an orderly transaction between market participants at the measurement date;

f.
Hamish Jiddiyyah – is the amount deposited as a security against fulfillment of a contract, or
promise, or completion of a transaction by one of the parties to other;

g.
Inventory – in relation to this standard is an asset held for sale in the ordinary course of
business or in the process of production for such sale;

h.
Murabaha – is sale of goods with an agreed upon profit mark-up on the cost. This could be
on a spot basis or deferred payment basis;

j.
Musawama – is a common bargain sale where the cost and profit elements are not
necessary to be disclosed. This could be on a spot basis or deferred payment basis;
